Perfect! I found the ai_local struct definitions. Let me analyze the byte offsets for both D1 and D2:

## D1 ai_local struct (from /Users/richard/code/ChocolateDescent/main_d1/aistruct.h, lines 134-156)

```c
typedef struct ai_local {
	int8_t			player_awareness_type;	//	offset 0
	int8_t			retry_count;			//	offset 1
	int8_t			consecutive_retries;	//	offset 2
	int8_t			mode;					//	offset 3
	int8_t			previous_visibility;	//	offset 4
	int8_t			rapidfire_count;		//	offset 5
	short			goal_segment;			//	offset 6-7
	fix			last_see_time, last_attack_time;
	fix			wait_time;
	fix			next_fire;
	fix			player_awareness_time;
	fix			time_player_seen;
	fix			time_player_sound_attacked;
	fix			next_misc_sound_time;
	fix			time_since_processed;
	vms_angvec	goal_angles[MAX_SUBMODELS];
	vms_angvec	delta_angles[MAX_SUBMODELS];
	int8_t			goal_state[MAX_SUBMODELS];
	int8_t			achieved_state[MAX_SUBMODELS];
} ai_local;
```

**D1 Byte Offsets:**
- **Offset 4**: `previous_visibility` (int8_t)
- **Offset 8**: Part of `last_see_time` (fix = int32, so offset 8 is the second fix field `last_attack_time`)

## D2 ai_local struct (from /Users/richard/code/ChocolateDescent/main_d2/aistruct.h, lines 147-173)

```c
typedef struct ai_local {
	int			player_awareness_type;	//	offset 0-3
	int			retry_count;			//	offset 4-7
	int			consecutive_retries;	//	offset 8-11
	int			mode;					//	offset 12-15
	int			previous_visibility;	//	offset 16-19
	int			rapidfire_count;		//	offset 20-23
	int			goal_segment;			//	offset 24-27
	fix			next_action_time;		//	offset 28-31
	fix			next_fire;				//	offset 32-35
	fix			next_fire2;				//	offset 36-39
	fix			player_awareness_time;	//	offset 40-43
	fix			time_player_seen;		//	offset 44-47
	fix			time_player_sound_attacked;
	fix			next_misc_sound_time;
	fix			time_since_processed;
	vms_angvec	goal_angles[MAX_SUBMODELS];
	vms_angvec	delta_angles[MAX_SUBMODELS];
	int8_t			goal_state[MAX_SUBMODELS];
	int8_t			achieved_state[MAX_SUBMODELS];
} ai_local;
```

**D2 Byte Offsets:**
- **Offset 4**: Part of `retry_count` (int = int32, so offset 4 is within retry_count, offset 4-7)
- **Offset 8**: Start of `consecutive_retries` (int = int32)

## Summary

The key difference is that D1 uses `int8_t` for the first 6 fields, making them 1 byte each, while D2 uses `int` (4 bytes) for all those fields:

| Offset | D1 | D2 |
|--------|----|----|
| 4 | `previous_visibility` (int8_t) | Bytes 4-7 of `retry_count` (int32) |
| 8 | `last_attack_time` (fix/int32) | Start of `consecutive_retries` (int32) |

