So the OCaml `do_ai_frame` doesn't handle retry_count/consecutive_retries at all. The C code at ai.cpp:973-975 does:

```c
if ((ailp->retry_count) && !(Game_mode & GM_MULTI)) {
    ailp->consecutive_retries += ailp->retry_count;
    ailp->retry_count = 0;
    if (ailp->consecutive_retries > 3) {
        // various mode-dependent actions...
    }
}
```

And later in the C code, consecutive_retries gets decremented. Let me look at more of this code block.


I need to port over the retry_count and consecutive_retries logic to the OCaml version, which currently skips this entirely. Let me trace through the full C implementation to understand all the places where these fields get modified.

